## Helper.eq() function

Performs a \[`SameValueZero`<!-- -->\](http://ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/\#sec-samevaluezero) comparison between two values to determine if they are equivalent.

 Lang

**Signature:**

```typescript
eq: (value: any, other: any) => boolean
```

<tr><td>

</td><td>

</td><td>

The other value to compare.


</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
**Returns:**

boolean

Returns `true` if the values are equivalent, else `false`<!-- -->.

## Example

var object = { 'user': 'fred' }<!-- -->; var other = { 'user': 'fred' }<!-- -->;

\_.eq(object, object); // =<!-- -->&gt; true

\_.eq(object, other); // =<!-- -->&gt; false

\_.eq('a', 'a'); // =<!-- -->&gt; true

\_.eq('a', Object('a')); // =<!-- -->&gt; false

\_.eq(NaN, NaN); // =<!-- -->&gt; true
